---
import DefaultLayout from '../layouts/DefaultLayout.astro'
const { src = '/CSorter.png' } = Astro.props
import Hero from '../components/Hero.astro'
import ContentMedia from '../components/ContentMedia.astro'
import Header from '../components/Header.astro'
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro'
---

<DefaultLayout title="How to Use CSorter">
  <Hero />

  <ContentMedia imgSrc="../public/CSorter2.png">
    <h2>Using CSorter Efficiently</h2>
    <p class="text-2xl">
      CSorter is a community-driven storage system designed to streamline item organization. When items are dropped into
      the input, CSorter automatically sorts them, ensuring a well-organized storage area. Whether you're a veteran
      player or new to the server, this guide will help you make the most out of the CSorter build.
    </p>
  </ContentMedia>

  <section class="mb-32 mt-64">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="mb-16 text-6xl">Get Started with CSorter</h2>
      <p class="text-2xl">
        Ready to contribute? Head over to <code class="copyable-text">/warp CSorter</code> now and start donating your items
        to help build a stronger community on AroundTheWorldMC. Everyone is welcome to contribute by donating items they
        no longer need and to retrieve what they require, fostering a collaborative and resourceful community environment.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-32 mt-64">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="mb-16 text-6xl">How CSorter Works</h2>
      <p class="text-2xl">
        CSorter simplifies item management by automatically sorting items dropped into its input. This process ensures
        that the storage area remains well-organized and accessible. By donating items you no longer need, you help
        maintain a useful inventory for everyone. Meanwhile, you can easily retrieve the items you require from the
        sorted storage.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <style>
    /* Styles for dark mode */
    .copyable-text {
      background-color: #333; /* Dark background to fit dark mode */
      color: #f0f0f0; /* Light text color for readability */
      padding: 4px 8px; /* Padding around the text */
      border-radius: 4px; /* Rounded corners */
      user-select: text; /* Make text selectable */
      cursor: text; /* Indicate that the text is selectable */
      font-family: monospace; /* Monospaced font for code appearance */
      border: 1px solid #555; /* Subtle border for better contrast */
    }

    .copyable-text::after {
      content: ''; /* Hint to copy text */
      font-size: 0.9em;
      color: #ccc; /* Slightly lighter color for the hint */
    }
  </style>
</DefaultLayout>
